notes.note:
Thank you for the estimate and the info .

Unfortunately, we do not cover clutches on our contracts thus the Dual Mass Flywheel won't be covered.
Darren Keeping
MISTER TRANSMISSION WINNIPEG 113 <mrt113@mistertransmission.com>
To : ​Darren Keeping
​
Hi Darren. When you replace a clutch on a manual transmission that has a dual mass flywheel the flywheel must be replaced. The reason that this is is because a DMF cannot be machined and therefore must be replaced. A standard manual transmission flywheel can be machined for a smooth surface for the new clutch but a Dual Mass Flywheel cannot be machined therefore must be replaced
Phil Dyck
Centre Manager
Mister Transmission
